  "prompt": "What are some animals native to New Zealand?",
  "response": "New Zealand is home to a variety of unique and native animals. Here are some of them:\n\n1. **Kiwi**: The kiwi is a flightless bird and a national symbol of New Zealand. There are five species of kiwi, all of which are native to the country.\n\n2. **K\u0101k\u0101p\u014d**: This is another flightless bird and the world's only flightless parrot. It is critically endangered and is found only in New Zealand.\n\n3. **Tuatara**: The tuatara is a reptile that is endemic to New Zealand. It is the only surviving member of its order, which makes it a unique species.\n\n4. **W\u0113t\u0101**: These are large insects native to New Zealand, with some species being among the heaviest insects in the world.\n\n5. **Kea**: The kea is a species of parrot found in the forested and alpine regions of the South Island. It is known for its intelligence and curiosity.\n\n6. **Hector's Dolphin**: This is the smallest dolphin species in the world and is found only in the coastal waters of New Zealand.\n\n7. **Kerer\u016b**: Also known as the New Zealand pigeon, this bird is known for its colorful plumage and significant role in seed dispersal.\n\n8. **Takah\u0113**: The takah\u0113 is a flightless bird that was once thought to be extinct but was rediscovered in 1948. It is now a protected species.\n\n9. **K\u014dkako**: This bird is known for its beautiful song and striking blue wattles. It is found in the forests of New Zealand.\n\n10. **Short-tailed Bat**: New Zealand is home to three species of native bats, including the short-tailed bat, which is unique for its ability to forage on the ground.\n\nThese animals highlight the biodiversity of New Zealand and many of them are protected due to their unique status and the threats they face from habitat loss and introduced species.",
